#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::community-of-practice_Slide1.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 1 - Contributing to GBIF’s community of practice*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:35
msgid ""
"In this video, I will explain how a growing community of volunteers "
"contributes to capacity development in the GBIF network, and how you can get "
"involved in these efforts to enable free and open access to biodiversity "
"data from all sources."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::community-of-practice_Slide2.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 2 - GBIF’s community of practice*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:41
msgid ""
"In addition to the formal network of GBIF Participants, a much larger "
"network of individuals and institutions is involved in GBIF activities – "
"both within and beyond GBIF’s formal Participant countries. These "
"individuals are involved in activities ranging from publishing biodiversity "
"data, to using GBIF-mediated data in research, to helping to improve data "
"quality, and to supporting others in learning how to benefit from GBIF."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:43
msgid "These individuals form GBIF’s community of practice."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:45
msgid ""
"Communities of practice are described by sociologists, Wegner and Trayner, "
"as “groups of people who share a concern or a passion for something they do "
"and learn how to do it better as they interact regularly.”"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:47
msgid ""
"The GBIF community of practice has emerged from the global network of "
"biodiversity practitioners due to their willingness to collaborate, share "
"knowledge, tools and standards, and support each other in progressing "
"towards the common goal of open biodiversity data contributing to research, "
"nature conservation and sustainable development."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:49
msgid ""
"This community has played a key role from the very beginning, even in the "
"origins of GBIF."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:51
msgid ""
"The GBIF Secretariat has a role in supporting the interactions between the "
"members of the community of practice and encouraging its development and "
"growth."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::community-of-practice_Slide3.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 3 - Volunteers*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:57
msgid ""
"We have categorized the different roles that individuals play in the "
"community."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:59
msgid ""
"This video will look at four different ways in which you can volunteer to "
"share your expertise to strengthen the GBIF community of practice, as either "
"a mentor, trainer, translator or biodiversity open data ambassador. These "
"roles are not mutually exclusive. Many people contribute through several of "
"these roles at the same time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::community-of-practice_Slide4.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:63
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 4 - Mentors*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:65
msgid ""
"Volunteer mentors are members of the GBIF community that have expertise in "
"areas covering data mobilization, data management, data analysis and use and "
"node management."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:67
msgid ""
"They share their expertise with new members of the community to help narrow "
"knowledge gaps."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:69
msgid ""
"Volunteer mentors provide support to teams working on projects funded "
"through programmes such as the Biodiversity Information for Development "
"(BID) programme."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:71
msgid ""
"They also support individuals and institutions in the community that need "
"help getting started with data mobilization, data management and data use."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:73
msgid ""
"During training workshops, we invite mentors to assist the trainers by "
"working with groups of participants to support them in their learning."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:75
msgid ""
"Node manager mentors are experienced members of existing GBIF nodes that "
"provide support to new GBIF nodes in getting established."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::community-of-practice_Slide5.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 5 - Trainers*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:81
msgid ""
"Some volunteer mentors also become trainers, providing training to new "
"members of the GBIF community."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:83
msgid ""
"Working with the GBIF Secretariat, trainers help to design reusable training "
"materials and curricula that form the basis of GBIF’s capacity enhancement "
"workshops."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:85
msgid ""
"Trainers provide training both onsite and online, and many of their trainees "
"go on to become mentors themselves, and may even act as trainers in "
"replication workshops."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:86
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::community-of-practice_Slide6.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:89
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 6 - Ambassadors*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:91
msgid ""
"Biodiversity open data ambassadors are biodiversity professionals who help "
"promote the principles and best practices of open data sharing and use "
"within their professional communities."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:93
msgid ""
"This includes communicating the benefits and opportunities provided by free "
"and open access to biodiversity data, as well as the importance of "
"responsible use of such data through proper citation and attribution."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:95
msgid ""
"Ambassadors can help engage research and policy communities beyond those "
"that can be reached by the GBIF nodes and Secretariat."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:97
msgid ""
"The Secretariat supports ambassadors by providing slides and promotional "
"materials for use at conferences, as well as feedback on abstracts and "
"presentations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::community-of-practice_Slide7.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:101
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 7 - Translators*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:103
msgid ""
"Finally, translators play a role that is essential for engaging GBIF’s "
"global network."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:105
msgid ""
"Most of the translation of GBIF’s website and materials is carried out by "
"volunteer translators from the community of practice."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:107
msgid ""
"In addition to their language skills, these translators have the domain "
"knowledge that helps them communicate GBIF as effectively as possible across "
"languages, allowing GBIF to reach new audiences."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:108
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::community-of-practice_Slide8.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:111
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 8 - Get involved*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:113
msgid ""
"We are pleased to invite you to get involved in GBIF’s community of "
"practice. You can find further information on the GBIF website about how to "
"contribute as a volunteer mentor, biodiversity open data ambassador and "
"translator and you are welcome to contribute in more that one of these "
"roles. The community of practice is your community – please let us know your "
"ideas on how we can develop it further."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:115
msgid "Thank you and we look forward to working with you very soon."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:119
#, no-wrap
msgid "Volunteer"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:122
msgid ""
"We encourage you to consider whether you can contribute to the GBIF "
"community of practice in any of these roles. We would welcome your https://"
"www.survey-xact.dk/LinkCollector?key=4S38YXU4U1CK[application^]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:124
msgid ""
"You are also welcome to contact us at volunteers@gbif.org to discuss how you "
"can contribute."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:125
#, no-wrap
msgid "Capacity enhancement and funding opportunities"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:129
msgid ""
"GBIF is a growing global network of Participant countries, economies and "
"organizations, each with different priorities and capacity assets and "
"needs.  Capacity enhancement is recognized as essential to underpin the "
"sustainable performance of the GBIF Participant network and all its members, "
"independent of their level of development."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:133
msgid ""
"Broadly speaking, much of GBIF’s work contributes to capacity enhancement.  "
"The Participant nodes ensure capacity development at the national level, "
"often providing training for individuals and institutions within their "
"networks.  Collaboration between Participants through GBIF’s governance "
"structures enables further international and regional exchange and "
"partnerships."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:135
#, no-wrap
msgid "Training participants at the Node Management workshop in Trinidad 2019 by Mélianie Raymond (licensed under https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0[CC-BY 4.0])"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:136
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::community-of-practice.jpg"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:141
msgid ""
"The GBIF Secretariat supports the work of the network, which contributes to "
"capacity development, in particular by coordinating activities, engaging "
"volunteers in the community of practice and supporting the development of "
"core training materials.  The Secretariat’s role in capacity enhancement "
"activities leans more toward facilitation than implementation: providing "
"guidance, documenting best practices, collating training material, "
"coordinating activities, and creating or aligning opportunities.  The "
"Secretariat plays a further role in enhancing capacity by providing funding "
"opportunities for collaborative projects in the network, often with a focus "
"on mobilizing biodiversity data, supporting the use of GBIF-mobilized data "
"and strengthening national biodiversity information facilities."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:143
msgid ""
"You can find more information about GBIF’s https://www.gbif.org/resource/"
"search?contentType=programme[funding programmes^] on our website."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:144
#, no-wrap
msgid "Engaging with GBIF"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:147
msgid ""
"Communication activities play a key role in strengthening and supporting the "
"GBIF network by enhancing visibility, knowledge exchange and engagement "
"across the community. Please stay in contact with GBIF to keep up with "
"events, opportunities, new features and other news."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:148
#, no-wrap
msgid "Newsletter"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:151
msgid ""
"Subscribe to the https://www.gbif.org/newsletters[GBIF newsletter^], a "
"compilation of news, events and opportunities, shared via email every couple "
"of months."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:152
#, no-wrap
msgid "Social media"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:155
msgid ""
"Follow GBIF across the below social media accounts and feel free to tag "
"these to help amplify activity within your node/network. Examples of "
"activities to promote on social media and to tag GBIF include trainings, "
"events, celebratory posts, new datasets mobilized to GBIF and data use "
"examples."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:157
msgid "LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/company/gbif/[@gbif^]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:158
msgid "Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/gbifnews[@gbifnews^]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:159
msgid ""
"Mastodon: https://biodiversity.social/@gbif[@biodiversity.social/@gbif^]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:160
msgid "Bluesky: https://bsky.app/profile/gbif.org[@gbif.org^]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:161
#, no-wrap
msgid "Events"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:164
msgid ""
"Regular events include sessions of the https://www.gbif.org/data-use-"
"club[Data Use Club^], the https://www.gbif.org/technical-support-"
"hour[Technical Support Hour for nodes^] and other webinars covering topics "
"of interest for the wider GBIF community."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/community-of-practice.adoc:166
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can keep track of events relevant to the network in the https://www.gbif.org/resource/search?contentType=event[GBIF events calendar^]. If you are arranging or have knowledge an event that is relevant and open to the GBIF community   (i.e. is not a closed event), please https://forms.gle/SLDP6senbxJQsauF8[notify^] the GBIF Secretariat to have your event included on the events calendar.\n"
msgstr ""

